web/src/containers/auth/Login.jsx.message:
This wont work because the method is not binded to the component

What you want is 

onLoginButtonClick = (event) => {
    event.preventDefault()
    userManager.signinRedirect()
}

or bind your method in the constructor

constructor(props) {
    super(props);
    // This binding is necessary to make `this` work in the render method
    this.onLoginButtonClick = this.onLoginButtonClick.bind(this);
  }

I prefer the first one. Just you need to understand that the this is binded automatically thanks to the ES6 arrow function () => ()

